/* STDLIB/iii/katabasis/doxa.iii -- THE BELIEF ORGAN: a type system for belief
 * enforced as law.  The mind keeps TWO BOOKS it is constitutionally forbidden
 * to blur:
 *
 *   THE MODAL BOOK        what is POSSIBLE and askable -- here, the heart's own
 *                         jurisdiction (adopted, runnable, evidence-reachable
 *                         cells; joint speculation held as cassandra colors,
 *                         hard-capped at 64).  Only this book may be ASSERTED
 *                         from, and every assertion is a STAKE.
 *   THE STATISTICAL BOOK  what has been OBSERVED -- exact integer tallies per
 *                         context, folded from the event log.  This book may
 *                         only PREFER (order, rank, recommend).  A statistical
 *                         preference promoted to a modal assertion is the
 *                         definition of a hallucination; here that promotion is
 *                         a REFUSED, COUNTED, CERTIFICATED door.
 *
 * THE LEDGER: every assertion stakes bits on a per-context account.  A correct
 * collapse EARNS the stake; a wrong collapse pays it as DEFICIT (the ANASTASIS
 * stance: the bits are exact and real, the joules symbolic).  THE SOLVENCY
 * LAW: a context's simultaneous open stakes are bounded by its balance (floor
 * 1, never 0 -- chronic mispredictors become reflexes, never corpses;
 * imagination is EARNED).
 *
 * THE FOREIGN LAW (kardia's monotone law, inherited): only a DERIVED record --
 * the heart re-ran the claim and saw the exit itself -- may settle a stake.
 * ADOPTED / foreign claims may seed standing but can never reconcile an
 * assertion.  Refused, counted, certificated.
 *
 * THE DREAM LAW (Bennett, made auditable): a dream is a reversible excursion
 * over the proven bijection (aether/entangle over aether/admix).  The walk is
 * exactly rewound and the books' fold is proven BIT-IDENTICAL before anything
 * is retained; the only bits kept are the certificate (a conjecture, always
 * printed unadjudicated).  A sabotaged rewind is DETECTED and refused -- the
 * zero-cost claim has teeth.
 *
 * THE RIGHT TO BE FORGOTTEN: unlearning = a TOMBSTONE fold-subtraction, proven
 * bit-identical inside the door against an independent shadow refold of the
 * log without the event.  A settlement may be forgotten; a stake with a live
 * settlement may NOT (the dangling-settlement refusal) -- forget the outcome
 * first, then the bet.
 *
 * THE QUESTION ECONOMY: over an enumerated world-set the worst-case
 * elimination of every available question is EXACTLY computable; the best
 * question is a theorem (proven by exhaustion in the self-proof).  An empty
 * question set is UNDECIDABLE-HERE, certificated -- the Goedel/halting answer:
 * stranded-in-doxa is a certified first-class state, never a guess.
 *
 * THE CITIZEN LAW: the mind exists only under a coherent constitution --
 * autognosis_root()==0 refuses the organ; cassandra's own self-proof is
 * re-proven as a condition of THIS organ's motion (the mind proves its
 * imagination's laws before it may believe anything).
 *
 * NO GATE, NO KAT, NO STANDING ARM -- like the heart itself: verification
 * lives INSIDE (dx_selfprove at every invocation: every law a positive arm AND
 * a negative control, incl. the two-path shadow refold and the events-vs-rows
 * conservation identity) and in the LIVE loop (predict -> the heart beats ->
 * reconcile), where the evidence is written by machinery this organ cannot
 * parameterize.  THE HEART AUDITS THE MIND.
 *
 * NIH: composes oneiros/cassandra (colored superposition), aether/entangle +
 * aether/admix (the proven bijection), katabasis/autognosis (constitution),
 * numera/idfold (the identity seat), aether/lagrangian (lg_noise/lg_action),
 * msvcrt.  Hexad: kind_essence.  Ring R0. */
module katabasis_doxa

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn fopen(path: u64, mode: u64) -> u64 from "msvcrt"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn fread(buf: u64, sz: u64, n: u64, stream: u64) -> u64 from "msvcrt"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn fputs(s: u64, stream: u64) -> i32 from "msvcrt"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn fclose(stream: u64) -> i32 from "msvcrt"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn _mkdir(path: u64) -> i32 from "msvcrt"

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn cass_selfproof() -> u64 from "cassandra.iii"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn cass_reset(acc: u64) -> i32 from "cassandra.iii"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn cass_add_color(delta: u64) -> u64 from "cassandra.iii"
